> Whipping up a compound butter is one of our favorite ways to add big flavor to any dish. Here, we blend the butter with Old Bay Seasoning, then dollop it over seared chicken for rich, smoky, peppery notes. It's finished with a scallion pan sauce, then paired with sides of roasted green beans and carrots and creamy, garlicky mashed potatoes.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{1%clove}. Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; slice into green-bean-size pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place potatoes and garlic in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{2%tbsp} and 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Roasted Veggies ==

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Toss carrots and green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until veggies are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Old Bay Butter ==

Meanwhile, to #bowl{} with softened butter, add ½ tsp @Old Bay Seasoning{1%tsp} (you'll use more in the next step) and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste; mix to combine.

> TIP: If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 10 seconds.

== Chicken and Pan Sauce ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with 1 tsp Old Bay Seasoning (2 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in 1 TBSP plain @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

== To Serve ==

If necessary, reheat mashed potatoes with a splash of potato cooking liquid over low heat for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide mashed potatoes, chicken, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with pan sauce, then dollop with Old Bay butter. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> TIP: Top potatoes with some of the sauce or Old Bay butter if you like!